definition.value: A member of the class of furans that is furan substituted by methyl, acetyl and methyl groups at positions 2, 3 and 5, respectively.
A lactam obtained by formal cyclocondensation of creatine. It is a metabolite of creatine.
Any pyrazine carrying one or more oxo substituents.

A branched amino octasaccharide consisting of a linear pentasaccharide comprising N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosamine, beta-D-galactose, two L-glycero-alpha-D-manno-heptose (L-alpha-D-Hep) residues and a 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulose (alpha-Kdo) residue linked in sequence (1->4), (1->3),(1->3) and (1->5), to the L-alpha-D-Hep residue proximal to the reducing end is also linked (1->4) a beta-D-glucose residue, while the galactose residue also carries an N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminic acid residue via a (2->3) linkage and the alpha-Kdo residue also carries a second alpha-Kdo residue linked (2->-4). One of a number of chemoenzymatically synthesised oligosaccharides composed of the inner core oligosaccharide of Campylobacter jejuni extended by various ganglioside mimics.

A branched amino nonasaccharide consisting of a linear hexasaccharide comprising beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-galactosamine, beta-D-galactose, two L-glycero-alpha-D-manno-heptose (L-alpha-D-Hep) residues and a 3-deoxy-alpha-D-manno-oct-2-ulose (alpha-Kdo) residue linked in sequence (1->3), (1->4), (1->3), (1->3) and (1->5), to the L-alpha-D-Hep residue proximal to the reducing end is also linked (1->4) a beta-D-glucose residue, while the galactose residue proximal to the reducing end also carries an N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminic acid residue via a (2->3) linkage and the alpha-Kdo residue also carries a second alpha-Kdo residue linked (2->-4). One of a number of chemoenzymatically synthesised oligosaccharides composed of the inner core oligosaccharide of Campylobacter jejuni extended by various ganglioside mimics.

A carbobicyclic compound that is (3aS,7aS)-octahydro-1H-indene substituted by a methyl group at positions 1S, 6 and 6, and by a 1-hydroxypropan-2-ylidene group at position 4. It is a sesquiterpenoid produced by a Trichoderma terpene cyclase.
A dichlorophenol that is phenol carrying chloro substituents at positions 2 and 4.
